chive-date=March 18, 2020|work=[[Casper Star-Tribune]]|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200318223119/https://trib.com/news/state-and-regional/first-coronavirus-case-reported-in-wyoming/article_0b075aea-a3ab-58d8-b5bd-a5b03b764075.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"LA Times\">{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-03-19/coronavirus-wyoming-covid-19-casper-idaho|title=Think the most isolated corners of the U.S. are safe from coronavirus? Think again|first=Maria L.|last=La Ganga|newspaper=[[LA Times]]|date=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* March 13, 2020: Second reported case is a man in Fremont County.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://trib.com/news/state-and-regional/second-wyoming-case-of-coronavirus-identified/article_1945cbeb-a94d-542d-b08c-26c3fa58dc2f.html|title=Second Wyoming case of coronavirus identified|date=13 March 2020|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200318222952/https://trib.com/news/state-and-regional/second-wyoming-case-of-coronavirus-identified/article_1945cbeb-a94d-542d-b08c-26c3fa58dc2f.html|work=Casper Star-Tribune|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* March 15, 2020: Governor Gordon recommends closing all public schools.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oilcity.news/community/health/covid-19/2020/03/15/natrona-county-school-district-closing-schools-starting-monday-amid-covid-19-pandemic/|title=Natrona County School District Closind Schools Starting Monday Amid COVID-19 Pandemic|date=15 March 2020|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-date=March 16, 2020|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200316131645/https://oilcity.news/community/health/covid-19/2020/03/15/natrona-county-school-district-closing-schools-starting-monday-amid-covid-19-pandemic/|work=Oil City News|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* March 18, 2020: Third positive case in [[Cheyenne, Wyoming]], brings the state count up to 16 confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://trib.com/news/local/casper/third-person-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-in-cheyenne-bringing-state/article_2b32b003-f677-512e-9286-e8c4de4988c3.html|date=18 March 2020|access-date=18 March 2020|title=Third person tests positive for coronavirus in Cheyenne, bringing state total to 16|work=Casper Star-Tribune|archive-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200318223539/https://trib.com/news/local/casper/third-person-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-in-cheyenne-bringing-state/article_2b32b003-f677-512e-9286-e8c4de4988c3.html|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Responses==\nOn March 17, Wyoming Governor [[Mark Gordon (politician)|Mark Gordon]] \"announced the creation of five task forces designed to tackle the effects of the spreading coronavirus\", and condemned [[Hoarding (economics)|hoarding]] in the state.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://trib.com/news/state-and-regional/health/wyoming-governor-announces-creation-of-five-task-forces-to-battle/article_428b9637-01b9-5533-ba53-af7a14542ce2.html|title=Wyoming governor announces creation of five task forces to battle effects of coronavirus|first1=Seth|last1=Klamann|first2=Morgan|last2=Hughes|publisher=[[Casper Star-Tribune]]|date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIndustries have had varying responses, with energy companies in the state trying to balance safety with continued productivity by imposing quarantine and travel restrictions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://trib.com/business/energy/energy-companies-in-wyoming-intensify-response-to-coronavirus-outbreak/article_6fd14076-9f24-5655-8967-60ef7488b590.html|title=Energy companies in Wyoming intensify response to coronavirus outbreak|first=Camille|last=Erickson|publisher=Casper Star-Tribune|date=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Impact on sports==\nIn college sports, the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] cancelled all winter and spring tournaments, most notably the [[NCAA Division I|Division I]] [[2020 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|men]]'s and [[2020 NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Tournament|women]]'s basketball tournaments, affecting colleges and universities statewide.<ref name=\"ncaa\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ncaa.org/about/resources/media-center/news/ncaa-cancels-remaining-winter-and-spring-championships |title=NCAA cancels remaining winter and spring championships |last=Osburn |first=Stacey |date=March 12, 2020 |website=NCAA |access-date=March 25, 2020}}</ref> On March 16, the [[National Junior College Athletic Association]] also canceled the remainder of the winter seasons as well as the spring seasons.<ref>{{Cite news |last=DeCamp |first=Scott |url=https://www.mlive.com/sports/2020/03/njcaa-cancels-spring-sports-basketball-nationals-amid-coronavirus-outbreak.html |title=NJCAA cancels spring sports, basketball nationals amid coronavirus outbreak |date=2020-03-16 |work=MLive.com |access-date=2020-03-25 |language=en}}</ref> High school sports were also cancelled.<ref name=\"LA Times\"/>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:right\"\n! colspan=\"4\" |2019 Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) Cases in Wyoming\nUpdated April 21, 2020<ref>{{cite web |title=COVID-19 Map and Statistics |url=https://health.wyo.gov/publichealth/infectious-disease-epidemiology-unit/disease/novel-coronavirus/covid-19-map-and-statistics/ |website=Wyoming Department of Health |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | County\n! scope=\"col\" | Confirmed Cases\n!Suspected Cases\n! scope=\"col\" | Deaths\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Albany County, Wyoming|Albany]]\n| 6\n|0\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Big Horn County, Wyoming|Big Horn]]\n| 1\n|1\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Campbell County, Wyoming|Campbell]]\n| 14\n|4\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Carbon County, Wyoming|Carbon]]\n|4\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Converse County, Wyoming|Converse]]\n| 9\n|6\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Crook County, Wyoming|Crook]]\n| 4\n|1\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Fremont County, Wyoming|Fremont]]\n|